==English==

===Etymology===
From Dutch ''[[tafereel]]'', a panel, picture,  diminutive of ''tafel'', table. Dutch from the Latin ''tabula'', table.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A carved [[panel]]
#{{nautical}} The flat upper part of a ship's [[stern]] above the [[transom]], often [[decorated]] with [[carving]]s
#{{nautical}} The [[taffrail]]

